stylometry: Sensitivity analysis can solve a problem with a lot of cells. Like the problem we did in class with all of the cities. Its able to solve a problem over a large area and find the best solution within it. By changing one cell, it can detect the best solution for the problem. Its important because it can expand its information over a large table and can show you the best solution if you change the original problem to something else. SolverTable is used for sensitivity analysis among other things. It consists of changing cells and constraints. It can also find how to maximize something or find the minimal.
